    <title>Syria contributor: Mona Alami</title>
    <description>French-Lebanese journalist Mona Alami has done extensive research on radical Islamist movements in Palestinian refugee camps, Salafi movements, Hezbollah and al-Qaida. She is a nonresident fellow at the Atlantic Council’s Rafik Hariri Center for the Middle East and a frequent commentator on political and economic issues in the Arab world, ranging from Lebanese politics to the battle for Aleppo. She’s on Twitter: @monaalami.
</description>
